com.stormpath.sdk.authc

Interface UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AuthenticationRequestBuilder<UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultUsernamePasswordRequestBuilder

    public interface UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder
extends AuthenticationRequestBuilder<UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder>
    A Builder to construct username/password-based AuthenticationRequests. It optionally supports specifying an specific account store as well for targeted authentication behavior.
    Since:
    1.0.RC5
    See Also:
    UsernamePasswordRequests.builder()

      • inAccountStore

        UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder inAccountStore(AccountStore accountStore)
        Sets a specific AccountStore that should process this authentication request, or null if the application's default account store authentication flow should execute. If non-null, the account store must be assigned to the application sending the request.

        This is an optional property, so the default is null, reflecting an application's default authentication flow.

        Usage

        Most applications will not need to specify an AccountStore during an authentication attempt, but specifying one can be useful in some cases, such as when an Application has many (dozens or hundreds) of assigned account stores: in this case specifying an account store will result in a direct (targeted) authentication which would be faster because Stormpath does not need to iteratively try each assigned account store as documented.

        Note that this property will be invalidated if a property is set in setOrganizationNameKey(String). Setting the latter will cause this property to be unused.

        Parameters:
        accountStore - a specific AccountStore that should process this authentication request, or null if the application's default account store authentication flow should execute. If non-null, the account store must be assigned to the application sending the request.
        Returns:
        this instance for method chaining.

      • withResponseOptions

        UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder withResponseOptions(BasicAuthenticationOptions options)
        Ensures that when the response is obtained, it will be retrieved with the specified options. This enhances performance by leveraging a single request to retrieve multiple related resources you know you will use.

        For example, it can be used to have the Account resource automatically expanded in the returned result.

        Parameters:
        options - the specific BasicAuthenticationOptions that will be used to customize the authentication response.
        Returns:
        this instance for method chaining.

      • setOrganizationNameKey

        UsernamePasswordRequestBuilder setOrganizationNameKey(String orgNameKey)
        Sets the Organization Name Key to be used as the account store.

        Note that this property cannot be used in conjunction to the inAccountStore(AccountStore) method. When the former is used it will invalidate any value set via the latter.

        Parameters:
        orgNameKey - An organization name key
        Returns:
        the instance of the method chaining
